{{infobox record label | name = Alpha & Omega Recording | image = | image_bg = | location = [[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], [[California|CA]] | founded = 1986 | founder = [[Sandy Pearlman]] | genre = all | country = [[United States|US]] | url = | }} '''Alpha & Omega Recording''' is the [[San Rafael, California]] recording studio of American music producer, [[Sandy Pearlman]].
Alpha & Omega Recording began in 1986, in Studio C at San Francisco's [[Hyde Street Studios]], which Pearlman leased until 1991 from the studio's owner, Dan Alexander.<ref name=hyde>{{cite web|title=Hyde Street Studios History: Unusual Tastes|url=http://www.hydestreet.com/history_unusual.html|accessdate=2011-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712233603/http://www.hydestreet.com/history_unusual.html|archive-date=2011-07-12|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref name=Garvey>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7iXXyenlU6sC&q=%22Popular+Metaphysics%22+Pearlman&dq=%22Popular+Metaphysics%22+Pearlman | title=Songwriter's market, 1991: where & how to market your songs | publisher=Writer's Digest Books | year=1990 | accessdate=June 30, 2011 | author=Garvey, Mark | page=273 | isbn=9780898794250 }}</ref> It is now located at 150 Bellam Street in San Rafael, California. The studio offers 72-track analog recording facilities with a [[Trident]] 52-channel console and a [[Pro Tools]] digital system for recording, editing, and mixing.<ref name=BreathingProtBkgrd>{{cite web|url=http://www.breathingprotection.com/sandy_pearlman.htm|title=Breathing Protection, Inc. Background|accessdate=2011-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708092230/http://www.breathingprotection.com/sandy_pearlman.htm|archive-date=2011-07-08|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
Notable artists who have recorded or mixed sounds at Alpha & Omega include [[Blue Öyster Cult]], [[Joe Satriani]], [[Forbidden Evil]], [[Angel Corpus Christi]], [[World Entertainment War]], [[Dysfunctional Family]], [[Mystical Fullmoon]], [[Exodus (band)|Exodus]], [[Katharine Chase]], [[Jennifer McKitrick]], [[Digital Underground]], [[John P. Hammond|John Hammond]], [[The Obsessed]], [[Todd Phillips (musician)|Todd Phillips]], [[Vio-Lence]], [[Howard Wales]], [[Patsy Moore]], and [[Manapsara]].
